&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/writing/domains/rhetoric-and-composition/terms/cliche/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/writing/domains/rhetoric-and-composition/terms/cliche/> ;
  schema:name "Cliché" ;
  schema:description "A ***cliché*** is a phrase or idea that has been used so often it no longer produces the effect it once did. \"Light at the end of the tunnel,\" \"think outside the box,\" \"at the end of the day\" — these were once vivid metaphors or fresh observations. Repetition has drained them. The reader's mind slides over a cliché without processing it, which means the writer has used words without communicating." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-06" ;
